commit.message:
Merge pull request #4 from nap/revert-3-patch-1

Revert "Fix in _get_matching_characters"

Update tox.ini

Added ignore for E402

Merge pull request #3 from hellrich/patch-1

Fix in _get_matching_characters

fixed _get_matching_characters

A limit of shorter/2 + 1 is used in StringUtils, this differs from Winklers paper (http://www.amstat.org/sections/srms/Proceedings/papers/1990_056.pdf), where a distance of longer/2 - 1 is used, corresponding to a limit for positions of longer/2 as in the changed code. Chnaged code now correctly works with the "CTRATE" - "TRACE" example from wikipedia

Fix in _get_matching_characters

The original code was biased towards the left side as a slice [i:j] does not contains the character at index j
